result.name: La Cucina Italiana

reviews.text:
Food was really good. Very flavourful and tasted like quality ingredients were used. Coffee is good too. 
Service was fantastic, very nice and knowledgeable staff! Hard to find that in Hong Kong.
Atmosphere is very homey and comfortable.

Quite a surprise for the quality Italian food here, definitely beyond my expectation! Pastas are surely signatures here, both the smoked salmon linguine and clams pasta in white wine sauce are done perfectly!! Al dente and really nice pasta quality! A very generous portion for the reasonable price too! Monday night was absolutely quiet, only us and another table the whole night on 2 floors (21 & 22/F)... the bread served in the beginning was warm which is good. The crispy pizza with mixed mushroom was a favorite of my friend, unexpectedly good Haha the cheese they use matches the pizza dough and tomato paste a lot, u wouldn't feel like a lot of ketchup in your mouth. ONE STAR OFF because there was a cockroach near our table appearing towards the end of our meal :(((( otherwise would have given full marks!
Great food, excellent service. Staff are friendly and attentive. Good for a warm family dinner.

When east meet west is fancy, then this time I define as classic. I like the atmosphere, which is romatic and classy.  Food in there is a but salty, but in general is above the standard.

I recommend seafood in lobster soup, which the seafood a fresh with a think lobster soup yummy.

However, I dun recommend dessert there, which the size is too small and not really delicious.  But they do serve nice coffee.

In general, we will still come back if there is a chance.

Very cozy decor with two floors with dining upstairs.  Menu has a great variety, spaghetti, risotto, gnocchi , salads, soups , mains, desserts etc.  Quite pricy but we ordered a main course and the dessert is free.  Complimentary peach nectar Bellini cocktails  even before we ordered.  Great service , knowledgeable waiters.  Tables quite far apart for intimate dinner dates.  Also very good value set dinners under $200.  I wouldn't say the food is authentic Italian but it's catered for the local`s palate.

reviews.text:
一個月一次既公司飯聚，又時候諗食咩🤔，聽朋友介紹QRE 21 樓有間吾錯既意大利🇮🇹餐廳🍴，決定聽佢講預約訂枱。

方便之處可以用WhatsApp 預訂座位，不過無訂座編號，不過吾緊要，有message show 番就可以。

平均set lunch 都係 HKD 118-158 （味包加一）
，但環境寬敞舒適，一行7人都可以安排大長枱👍🏽，裝修設計好有意大利🇮🇹庭園中，可以係咁打卡📍📷

上套餐之前會有脆脆地既多士/面包🥯供應，有芝士粉，牛油🐄，蒜蓉醬，吾會食厭🎈

叫左set daily special: 包雜菌湯🥣：賣相一般，味道都好普通，加左點點忌廉調味，還可以

烤牛排🥩配沙律🥗薯角🥔：牛排🥩要求5成熟，烤得好好，吾會話有太多血水滲出，牛味好濃，不過肥膏多，而且比較薄身，感覺吾太化算☘️
沙律🥗菜好新鮮，而且加埋黑醋汁，吾錯。雖然薯角厚🔪， 但無咩味，要加🧂黎配會易入口點。

跟一杯餐飲🥃☕️： 正常檸檬🍋茶，配上意大利🇮🇹旗仔，幾CUTE😍

食物環境衛生化算度都吾錯，會再黎光顧😶

Food was really good. Very flavourful and tasted like quality ingredients were used. Coffee is good too. 
Service was fantastic, very nice and knowledgeable staff! Hard to find that in Hong Kong.
Atmosphere is very homey and comfortable.
傳統意大利食品，意式裝修，傾計好地方。

Quite a surprise for the quality Italian food here, definitely beyond my expectation! Pastas are surely signatures here, both the smoked salmon linguine and clams pasta in white wine sauce are done perfectly!! Al dente and really nice pasta quality! A very generous portion for the reasonable price too! Monday night was absolutely quiet, only us and another table the whole night on 2 floors (21 & 22/F)... the bread served in the beginning was warm which is good. The crispy pizza with mixed mushroom was a favorite of my friend, unexpectedly good Haha the cheese they use matches the pizza dough and tomato paste a lot, u wouldn't feel like a lot of ketchup in your mouth. ONE STAR OFF because there was a cockroach near our table appearing towards the end of our meal :(((( otherwise would have given full marks!
環境不錯，味道很好。午餐質素合理。
